   Mesa Southwest Museum:
   ``The Train Show: 100 Years of Model Railroading.'' Through Feb.
25.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>SAN FRANCISCO</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   M.H. de Young Memorial Museum:
   ``California Colorists: Society of Six.'' Through Dec. 31.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>HOUSTON</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   Museum of Fine Arts:
   ``The Grand Elegance Venice: Costumes of Mariano Fortuny.'' More
than 50 gowns, costumes and accessories created by Venetian
painter, engraver, theater designer and photographer Fortuny
(1871-1949). Through Dec. 31.
   ``Masterworks of Chinese Paintings From the Forbidden City.''
Through Dec. 31.
   ``The Intimate Interiors of Edouard Vuillard.'' Through Jan. 28.
